{
  "page": "Morning",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the warship, see <a href=\"/index.php/Morning_Tide\" title=\"Morning Tide\">Morning Tide</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/50px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/75px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/100px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Morning</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/50px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/75px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/100px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Ertac_Altinoz-Morning01.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Ertac Altinoz-Morning01.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/16/Ertac_Altinoz-Morning01.jpg/350px-Ertac_Altinoz-Morning01.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"197\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/16/Ertac_Altinoz-Morning01.jpg/525px-Ertac_Altinoz-Morning01.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/16/Ertac_Altinoz-Morning01.jpg/700px-Ertac_Altinoz-Morning01.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Morning in the ruins of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonpit\" title=\"Dragonpit\">Dragonpit</a>, by Ertaç Altınöz ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Rider</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Species</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">Dragon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Gender</th><td>\nFemale</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Colors</th><td>\npale pink scales<br />black crest and horns</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Hatched</th><td>\nIn&#160;late <a href=\"/index.php/130_AC\" title=\"130 AC\">130&#160;AC</a>-early <a href=\"/index.php/131_AC\" title=\"131 AC\">131&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Cal_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Cal-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>,&#160;the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\nIn&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/136_AC\" title=\"136 AC\">136</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_153_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">153&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Cal_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Cal-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Parent</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Syrax\" title=\"Syrax\">Syrax</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Morning</b> was a she-<a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> that hatched during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>. She belonged to Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a>, the daughter of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a> and Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Laena_Velaryon\" title=\"Laena Velaryon\">Laena Velaryon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Later_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Later life</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Known_dragonriders_of_Morning\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known dragonriders of Morning</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Morning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Morning\" title=\"Category:Images of Morning\">Images of Morning</a></div>\n<p>Morning's scales were pale pink, and she had a black crest and horns.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> During the third month of <a href=\"/index.php/135_AC\" title=\"135 AC\">135&#160;AC</a>, Morning had grown big enough for Rhaena to ride.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Morning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Morning_by_Fkaluis.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/26/Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Morning_by_Fkaluis.jpg/350px-Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Morning_by_Fkaluis.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/26/Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Morning_by_Fkaluis.jpg/525px-Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Morning_by_Fkaluis.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/26/Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Morning_by_Fkaluis.jpg/700px-Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Morning_by_Fkaluis.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Morning_by_Fkaluis.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Morning and <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a>, by Fkaluis ©</div></div></div> \n<p>Morning hatched during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a> from one of the three <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon eggs</a> that Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a> brought with her to the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vale\">Vale</a>, a clutch produced by Rhaenyra's she-dragon <a href=\"/index.php/Syrax\" title=\"Syrax\">Syrax</a>. News of Morning's birth reached the <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a> around the start of <a href=\"/index.php/131_AC\" title=\"131 AC\">131&#160;AC</a>, greatly troubling them, as they had lost all of their dragons during the fighting. Dowager Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a> feared that the <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> would consider the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a> as more legitimate, due to Morning's birth.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The war lasted only for another half a year, during which time Morning was still too young to be ridden.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Morning was one of four dragons to survive the Dance of the Dragons, and the only one still controlled by the Targaryens.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Rhaena and Morning arrived in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> after the death of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> in mid-<a href=\"/index.php/131_AC\" title=\"131 AC\">131&#160;AC</a>. While the <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> became ecstatic at the sight of Morning, Rhaena's brother, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>, who was fearful of dragons, paled when he saw the dragon for the first time and commanded his guards to \"get that wretched creature out of my sight.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During their time at King's Landing, Rhaena would often visit throughout the city, usually with Morning, who was still small and young, coiled about her shoulders like a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shawl#Stole\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Shawl\">stole</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> By the start of <a href=\"/index.php/134_AC\" title=\"134 AC\">134&#160;AC</a>, Morning had grown much and had made her lair in the ruins of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonpit\" title=\"Dragonpit\">Dragonpit</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> On the third day of the third month of <a href=\"/index.php/135_AC\" title=\"135 AC\">135&#160;AC</a>, Rhaena <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">rode upon</a> the back of Morning for the first time. They returned to the Dragonpit after circling once around the city, and subsequently went forth every day, flying farther each time. Rhaena landed Morning inside the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> on only one occasion, where Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Daenaera_Velaryon\" title=\"Daenaera Velaryon\">Daenaera Velaryon</a> was delighted by the dragon, but King Aegon III again refused to go and see the dragon. Shortly thereafter, Rhaena traveled on the dragon's back to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>, where, according to Rhaena, she and her dragon would be more welcome.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Rhaena's husband, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Corwyn_Corbray\" title=\"Corwyn Corbray\">Corwyn Corbray</a>, was killed in the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vale\">Vale</a> that same year, Rhaena's sister <a href=\"/index.php/Baela_Targaryen\" title=\"Baela Targaryen\">Baela</a> traveled to Dragonstone to ensure that Rhaena would not use Morning to attempt to avenge her husband's death.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/136_AC\" title=\"136 AC\">136&#160;AC</a>, preparations were being made for a <a href=\"/index.php/Royal_progress\" title=\"Royal progress\">royal progress</a> to he held after King Aegon III <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_majority\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Age of majority\">turned sixteen</a>. Rhaena desired to accompany the progress on Morning, but this suggestion was delicately deflected by the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> and the council of <a href=\"/index.php/Regency_of_Aegon_III\" title=\"Regency of Aegon III\">regents</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Later_life\">Later life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Morning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Later life\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>It is unknown when Morning died or why, but the event happened some time before the death of the <a href=\"/index.php/Last_dragon\" title=\"Last dragon\">last dragon</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_153_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">153&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Cal_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Cal-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_dragonriders_of_Morning\">Known dragonriders of Morning</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Morning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known dragonriders of Morning\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Morning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Cal-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Cal_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Cal_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Cal_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>See the <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest/Calculations_Ages_(Continued2)#Morning\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest/Calculations Ages (Continued2)\">Morning</a> calculation</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - The Voyage of Alyn Oakenfist.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\">3.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dr